ays not entirely consonant with its Western origins. Capitalism is not a free-floating entity -- it is a socially embodied phenomenon that needs to function in various cultural contexts. Consequently, the tension between the universal status that some claim capitalism now occupies in the post–Cold War world and the particularities of the local cultures it enters should be of great concern.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCapitalismxSocial aspectszSoutheast Asia. 0aCapitalism--Social aspects--Southeast Asia. 0aEconomic developmentxSocial aspectszSoutheast Asia. 0aEconomic development--Social aspects--Southeast Asia. 0aSocial valueszSoutheast Asia. 0aSocial values--Southeast Asia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aAlatas, Syed Farid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarker, Joshua David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerger, Mark T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoanantakool, Paritta Chalermpow, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLan, Goh Beng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalhotra, Kamal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWee, C. J. W. L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWee, C.J.W.-L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 ade Jesus, Edilberto C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102470708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z97831106630060